replacement for the LCRRPR and must begin production by FY 2030 to support HIMARS and MLRS crew training requirements. The JR3 program shall leverage
available rocket motor technologies to develop a new training rocket that results in a configuration that is affordable and supports the required production timeline. The
JR3 rocket shall be integrated into a launch pod container (LPC) that shall be compatible with current HIMARS and MLRS launchers. The JR3 effort is planned to award
under an Other Transactional Authority (OTA) in FY25 to conduct competitive prototyping of two candidate systems culminating in prototype flight testing and down-
select to a single solution in FY 2027. A follow-on qualification phase initiates in FY 2027 in support of a future production decision.




