A key factor for future force success is the ability to collect, process, and use information about an adversary while preventing similar information from being disclosed.
Trojan NexGEN is a combined operational and readiness mission system which uses advanced networking technology to provide seamless rapid radio relay, secure
communications to include voice, data, and electronic reconnaissance support to U.S. forces throughout the world. Trojan NexGEN operations may be easily tailored
to fit the Secretary of Defense and Chief of Staff priorities for military intelligence unit training and mission schedules and surged during specific events to involve every
aspect of the tactical intelligence collection, processing, analysis and reporting systems. Engineers test and evaluate new digital intelligence collection, processing and
dissemination technology using the fielded Trojan NexGEN systems prior to the acquisition of those technologies. As part of the Army Transformation Initiatives and
