Develop techniques to improve operational lethality and readiness by instrumenting emerging and legacy and future tactical
vehicles with available environmental monitoring technologies/sensors to record temperature, humidity, shock, and vibration
exposure to ensure ammunition is viable for use once it is issued from the Army accountable system. This development effort
will investigate various methods of ammunition health monitoring techniques and predicted remaining useful life algorithms of
past investments coupled with industry best practices of supply chain management. As these solutions are evaluated, the most


